    "Nectar (Zhu et al., 2023) is a large-scale preference dataset where GPT-4 ranks responses from seven different models.",
    "We convert each data point into 7 2 pairwise comparisons required by our BTL and BTL2 judges.",
    "We create our own training (83.9k data points) and test (21k data points) sets from their publicly available training set.",
    "We consider three types of metrics.",
    "For rating prediction tasks, we report the mean squared error (MSE), mean absolute error (MAE), and accuracy."
  ],
